# Git

## Rules

- Do not commit unless explicitly asked by the user
- Never commit `.env`, credentials, or `node_modules`
- Never force-push `main`/`master` unless explicitly requested
- Do not amend commits unless conditions in project git protocol are met

## Commit messages

- Complete sentences; focus on **why**
- Examples: `fix auth race before session ready`, `add pagination to users list`

## What to include in commits

- Source changes
- Prisma schema + migration SQL together
- `.env.example` updates for new env vars

## What to exclude

- `dist/`, `coverage/`, generated artifacts (unless project policy says otherwise)
- Local IDE settings

## Branches

- Feature branches off main
- PR review before merge to production

## Remote

Project may be disconnected from remote — do not push unless user asks.
